  "notes": "Shona (chiShona) — Bantu language of Zimbabwe; standard orthography (1955/1967 revision) in the Latin script. Regular and largely phonemic, with a five-vowel system /a e i o u/ and open (CV) syllables. Two Shona-specific series drive the digraphs: breathy-voiced obstruents written with ⟨h⟩ (bh, dh, mh, nh, vh, and the breathy g, j, z, zh) as against the implosives ⟨b⟩ /ɓ/ and ⟨d⟩ /ɗ/; and the whistled sibilants written with ⟨v⟩ (sv, zv, tsv, dzv, nzv). ⟨l⟩, ⟨q⟩ and ⟨x⟩ occur only in loanwords. Tone is phonemic but not written.",
